==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Two-name
<hw>Two"-name`</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Banking)</fld> <def>Having or
bearing two names; <as>as, <col><b>two-name paper</b></col>, that is,
negotiable paper on which at least two persons are severally liable as
separate makers, or, usually, one as maker and one as
indorser</as>.</def> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Two-parted</ent>⟦br⟧
